added.title: Campfire!
added.description: The Titans put on a show but Robin warns that the performance must be boring or else they'll wake up the wolves.

added.title: Communicate Openly
added.description: Bumbleebee becomes the 6th Titan and moves into the Tower but has a hard time adjusting.

added.title: Strength of a Grown Man
added.description: Needing a hero with shrinking powers, but forgetting about Bumblebee, Robin invites The Atom to join their fight against the Brain.

added.title: Girls Night In Part 1
added.description: The Girls Night Out Crew decide to stay in and have a slumber party but an unknown alien threat descends on Jump City.

added.title: Girls Night In Part 2
added.description: When Blackfire begins her plan to conquer Earth, the girls must pull out all the stops to defeat her.

added.title: Room for Ruby
added.description: Steven's Gem family continues to grow.

added.title: Same Old World
added.description: Steven flies around the world.

added.title: Steven Floats
added.description: Steven is so excited to be back home that he jumps for joy and jumps way too high.

added.title: Shirt Club
added.description: Steven and Buck Dewey make t-shirts together.

added.title: Joy Ride
added.description: The Cool Kids help Steven put some fun back in his life.

added.title: The Drama
added.description: Everyone assumes Darwin and Carrie's relationship is doomed as they're so different. That is, everyone except Darwin and Carrie. When Carrie's cool ghostly ex-boyfriend turns up, Gumball decides to get Darwin to confront what's really going on.

added.title: The Diet
added.description: Gumball and Darwin discover the reason Dad's diet wasn't working was that he was actually on ten diets and eating a meal for each of them. They eventually manage to help him lose weight, but Richard's newfound buffness also brings out his more obnoxious side.

added.title: The Fan
added.description: Sarah, the new kid in school, is Gumball and Darwin's number one, slightly obsessive, fan. Sarah is intensely following Gumball and Darwin around trying to win their friendship.  When Gumball tells her that she is acting like a stalker, she embraces it and actually takes it up a notch.  However, when Gumball and Darwin realise that she's behaving this way because she's lonely, they go to surprising lengths to make her feel accepted.

added.title: Special Delivery
added.description: Enid and Rad go on a road trip to deliver a package.

added.title: Wisdom, Strength, and Charisma
added.description: When Enid goes to a new school, KO sets out to make sure she fits in.

added.title: Are You Ready for Some Megafootball?!
added.description: Lakewood's Megafootball team takes on their rival in a big game.

added.title: Mystery Sleepover
added.description: KO, Enid and Rad attempt to solve a mystery.

added.title: You Are Rad
added.description: When KO forgets his name tag, Rad lets him use his, which results in everyone thinking KO is Rad, including Rad himself.

added.title: Don't Look
added.description: At the top of Dead Mountain, Finn discovers a treasure that comes with a terrible price.

added.title: Elemental
added.description: Ice King discovers something buried deep beneath the Ice Kingdom that could change Ooo forever.

added.title: Escape from the Citadel
added.description: Finn and Jake follow the Lich of the Citadel, where Finn meets his long lost dad. But just how far does the apple fall from the tree?

added.title: Expert or Liar
added.description: Rigby wants to redeem himself by winning on "Expert or Liar."

added.title: Earth & Water
added.description: Princess Bubblegum subjects Flame Princess to a series of tests to gauge Flame Princess's fiery tendencies. But when there's an emergency at the treehouse, and Princess Bubblegum leaves Cinnamon Bun to watch Flame Princess, her experiment might literally backfire in her face.

added.title: Fogata de campamento!
added.description: Los Titanes montan un espectáculo, pero Robin les advierte que la actuación debe ser aburrida o despertarán a los lobos.

added.title: Dungeon Train
added.description: All aboard! Finn and Jake discover a train where every car is a dungeon filled with a new foe for Finn to fight. Jake quickly gets bored and wants to leave, but Finn is having the BEST time and doesn't want to leave... ever!

added.title: Comunicacion abierta
added.description: Bumblebee se convierte en la sexta Titán y se muda a la torre, pero tiene problemas para adaptarse.

added.title: La fuerza de un hombre adulto
added.description: Necesitando un héroe con poderes para encogerse, Robin se olvida de Bumblebee e invita a Átomo a unirse a su pelea contra El Cerebro.

added.title: Noche de chicas Parte 1
added.description: El equipo de la Noche de Chicas decide quedarse en casa y celebrar una pijamada, pero una desconocida amenaza alienígena desciende sobre Jump City.

added.title: Noche de chicas Parte 2
added.description: Cuando Blackfire pone en marcha su plan para conquistar la Tierra, las chicas deben intentarlo todo para derrotarla.

added.title: Exit 9B
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are the only ones who can save the park after everyone gets brain washed.

added.title: Uncle Baseball
added.description: A failing little league team on the brink of giving up gets help from Uncle Grandpa and some Major League Baseball players.

added.title: Uncle Dummy
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve try to convince Mr. Gus that his ventriloquist dummy is alive.

added.title: Midnight Madness
added.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: Uncle Fashion
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a young boy who wants to be a fashion designer by taking him somewhere his style will be appreciated.

added.title: Our Brand is Chaos
added.description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

added.title: Fancy Restaurant
added.description: Muscle Man has to impress his girlfriend's parents at a fancy dinner.

added.title: Ello Gov'nor
added.description: After watching a scary movie about a British Taxi, the guys have to help Rigby overcome his fears.

added.title: Dr. Animo and the Mutant Ray
added.description: Dr. Animo has broken out of jail, and has been tracking down Ben, intent on revenge. At the same time, Ben's broken off a piece of the Omnitrix, and as a result, has turned into weird alien combinations, i.e. StinkArms.

added.title: The Tails of Mardrynia
added.description: After reading a book about a mystical animal society in class, Clarence is inspired to round up local animals and recreate an animal world of his own to cheer up his friend Percy. But will Percy take the game too far?

added.title: Uncle Grandpa at the Movies
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve cause a ruckus at the movies, Mr. Gus is forced to play the hero in order to save the day.

added.title: Clarence Wendle and the Eye of Coogan
added.description: Clarence and other students find the crusty old journal of Coogan filled with clues leading to a mysterious treasure. Clarence spearheads the team of treasure hunters to journey through the perils of Aberdale seeking the lost Eye of Coogan.

added.title: Game Show
added.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Babies
added.description: When the President calls in the Uncle Grandpa babies, they have to act quickly and use their special baby powers to defuse a missile.

added.title: Mystery Girl
added.description: After Clarence and pals call random numbers as a prank, Clarence ends up connecting with a girl and they strike up a friendship. But will this long distance phone pal last?

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Painbow
added.description: When a mysterious rainbow causes everyone to become unnaturally happy, the Powerpuff Girls must find where it ends to save the day and return Townsville to normal.

added.title: Power Up Puff
added.description: During a fight, both Buttercup and Bubbles are surprised to discover they've leveled up, leaving Blossom to wonder when or if she'll get new powers too.

added.title: Tiara Trouble
added.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

added.title: Presidential Punchout
added.description: When Morbucks enters the Student Body President race, Blossom sinks to her level to secure the win.

added.title: And Then There Were None
added.description: Vilgax and Eon team up to wipe out every Ben in every dimension!

added.title: The Vengers
added.description: Billy Billions, Kangaroo Kommando, and Captain Nemesis team up to take down Ben, and claim his place as protector of Bellwood?!?

added.title: The Rooters of All Evil
added.description: Meet the Rooters, the Black Ops wing of the Plumbers from the Null Void. They've come looking for someone close to Ben, and they mean business!

added.title: No Honor Among Bros
added.description: Rook is under the influence of Fistrick's "bro" essence, and starts to act like a bro. Can he and Ben infiltrate an alien fight club to claim the Golden Fist? (Introducing Slix Vigma, alien promoter.)

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!
